Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20need%20that%20long.%C2%A0Tuesday%E2%80%99s%20216-210%C2%A0for%20removal%20swiftly%20saw%20McCarthy%20gone%C2%A0after%20a%20motion%20to%20delay%20the%20vote%20failed%20just%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMcCarthy%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20as%20a%20comparatively%20moderate%20Republican%2C%20who%20has%20in%20some%20cases%20shown%20a%20willingness%20to%20compromise%20with%C2%A0President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20ultimately%20led%20to%20his%20downfall%20among%20conservatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ECompromise%20on%20budget%20and%20shutdown%20prompted%20attempted%20removal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%C2%A0on%20Tuesday%2C%20McCarthy%20announced%20that%20he%20intended%20to%20conduct%20the%20ballot%20in%20the%20chamber%E2%80%99s%20first%20round%20of%20votes%20in%20the%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20came%C2%A0just%20days%20after%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fus-avoids-shutdown-after-congress-passes-funding-bill%2Fa-66972589%5C%22%3Ethe%20passing%20of%20a%2045-day%2C%20stop-gap%20funding%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20avoid%20a%20government%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGaetz%20was%20angered%20that%20McCarthy%20passed%20the%20measure%20with%20Democratic%20votes%20and%20accused%20him%20of%20working%20for%20President%20Biden%2C%20and%20not%20his%20Republican%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20miffed%20that%20McCarthy%20had%20come%20to%20an%20agreement%20with%20Biden%20over%20further%20funding%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20despite%20such%20finances%20being%20struck%20from%20the%20emergency%2045-day%20bill%20known%20as%20a%20Continuing%20Resolution%2C%20or%20CR.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20Republicans%20opposed%20the%20idea%20of%20ousting%20McCarthy%2C%20as%20there%20was%20no%20clear%20plan%20in%20place%20for%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20eventuality%20of%20his%20removal.%20That%20was%20the%20motivation%20for%20their%20last-minute%20motion%20to%20table%20t