ew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20United%20States%20Commission%20on%20International%20Religious%20Freedom%20(USCIRF)%20has%20once%20again%20noted%20with%20concern%20that%20%E2%80%9Creligious%20freedom%20conditions%20in%20India%20have%20notably%20declined%20in%20recent%20years%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Fevents%2Fhearings%2Fadvancing-religious-freedom-within-us-india-bilateral-relationship-1%5C%22%3Ehearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%E2%80%98Advancing%20Religious%20Freedom%20within%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20India%20Bilateral%20Relationship%E2%80%99%20on%20September%2020%2C%20USCIRF%20highlighted%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20legal%20framework%20and%20enforcement%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdiscriminatory%20policies%20against%20religious%20minorities%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20press%20statement%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Fnews-room%2Freleases-statements%2Fuscirf-reiterates-concerns-religious-freedom-india-calls-release%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUSCIRF%20is%20an%20independent%2C%20bipartisan%20federal%20government%20entity%20established%20by%20the%20US%20Congress%20to%20monitor%2C%20analyse%2C%20and%20report%20on%20religious%20freedom%20abroad.%20The%20governmental%20body%20makes%20foreign%20policy%20recommendations%20to%20the%20President%2C%20the%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20and%20Congress%20intended%20to%20deter%20religious%20persecution%20and%20promote%20freedom%20of%20religion%20and%20belief.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20on%20September%2020%20discussed%20%E2%80%9Cenforced%20discriminatory%20policies%20targeting%20religious%20minorities%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fharyana-violence-mewat-hate-and-provocative-videos%5C%22%3Eviolence%20in%20Haryana%E2%80%99s%20Nuh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20targeted%20attacks%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcatholic-church-leaders-in-kerala-condemn-modi-govt-for-alleged-genocide-in-manipur%5C%22%3EChristians%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Findias-bnei-menashe-community-in-crisis-as-manipur-rocked-by-ethnic-violence%2F%5C%22%3EJewish%3C%2Fa%3E%20minorities%20in%20Manipur.%20The%20participants%20of%20the%20hearing%20offered%20policy%20options%20for%20the%20United%20States%20to%20work%20with%20India%20to%20combat%20abuses%20of%20religious%20freedom%20and%20related%20human%20rights%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReligious%20freedom%20conditions%20in%20India%20have%20notably%20declined%20in%20recent%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20USCIRF%20chair%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Fabraham-cooper%5C%22%3EAbraham%20Cooper%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fdata-rise-in-attacks-on-christians-in-india-up-four-times-in-11-years-2012-2022%5C%22%3EChristians%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dalits%2C%20and%20Adivasis%20are%20experiencing%20increased%20levels%20of%20attacks%20and%20acts%20of%20intimidation.%20Authorities%20have%20continued%20to%20suppress%20minority%20voices%20and%20those%20advocating%20on%20their%20behalf.%20These%20trends%2C%20and%20their%20implication%20for%20US%20foreign%20policy%2C%20should%20not%20be%20ignored.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20body%20also%20called%20for%20the%20release%20of%20religious%20prisoners%20in%20India.%20According%20to%20USCIRF%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Fvictims-list%2F%5C%22%3EFrank.%20R%20Wolf%20Freedom%20of%20Religion%20or%20Belief%20Victims%20List%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20public%20database%2C%20a%20total%20of%2037%20individuals%20across%20multiple%20faiths%20have%20been%20jailed%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpeaceful%20exercise%20of%20their%20freedom%20of%20religion%20or%20belief%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20participants%20drew%20attention%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-riots-fir-meeran-haider%5C%22%3EMeeran%20Haider%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-was-independent-journalist-rupesh-kumar-singh-arrested-for-his-reportage%5C%22%3ERupesh%20Singh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20have%20been%20imprisoned%20for%20protesting%20against%20the%20deterioration%20of%20religious%20freedom%2C%20the%20press%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHairder%2C%20a%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%20student%20and%20a%20youth%20leader%20of%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20special%20cell%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20in%20connection%20with%20his%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20violence%20in%20North%20East%20Delhi%20in%20February%202020.%20Singh%2C%20an%20independent%20journalist%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20Jharkhand%20Police%20on%20July%2017%2C%202022%2C%20for%20his%20alleged%20links%20with%20the%20outlawed%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Maoist).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaider%20was%20targeted%20for%20leading%20peaceful%20protests%20against%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20and%20was%20charged%20with%20offences%20under%20the%20UAPA%20%5BUnlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20%5D.%20Singh%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20known%20for%20his%20reporting%20on%20state%20violence%20and%20discrimination%20against%20Adivasis.%20He%20has%20been%20detained%20since%20July%202022%2C%20also%20under%20the%20UAPA%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20USCIRF%20vice-chair%20Frederick%20A.%20Davie.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUSCIRF%20calls%20on%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20evaluate%20these%20cases%20and%20to%20release%20all%20prisoners%20of%20conscience%20and%20those%20detained%20for%20peacefully%20expressing%20their%20religion%20or%20belief.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20June%202020%2C%20USCIRF%20has%20called%20on%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20to%20designate%20India%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9CCountry%20of%20Particular%20Concern%E2%80%9D%20fo