increasingly%20seen%20as%20a%20major%20potential%20public%20health%20problem.%20Bedbugs%20have%20in%20recent%20weeks%20gone%20from%20being%20a%20subject%20of%20potential%20derision%20to%20a%20contentious%20political%20issue%20in%20France%2C%20with%20aghast%20citizens%20reporting%20seeing%20the%20creatures%20in%20locations%20including%20trains%2C%20the%20Paris%20metro%20and%20cinemas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ffrance-to-hold-crisis-meetings-on-bedbug-scourge%2Farticleshow%2F104151750.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ffrance-to-hold-crisis-meetings-on-bedbug-scourge%2Famp_articleshow%2F104151750.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ffrance-to-hold-crisis-meetings-on-bedbug-scourge%2Famp_articleshow%2F104151750.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Entrepreneur%20Vivek%20Wadhwa's%20New%20Company%20To%20Use%20Breath%20To%20Detect%20Cancer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20five%20years%20Vivek%20Wadhwa%2C%20an%20entrepreneur%20and%20academic%20who's%20well%20known%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20has%20been%20working%20on%20a%20longshot%20project%20to%20detect%20cancer%20in%20people%20using%20only%20their%20breath%20-%20similar%20to%20using%20a%20breathalyzer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wadhwa's%20new%20company%2C%20which%20has%20not%20been%20previously%20reported%2C%20is%20called%20Vionix%20Biosciences%20Inc.%20Its%20goal%20of%20collecting%20health%20information%20in%20a%20less%20invasive%20way%20has%20long%20been%20a%20dream%20of%20technologists.%20See%3A%20Elizabeth%20Holmes'%20failed%20blood-testing%20startup%20Theranos.%20But%20unlike%20Holmes%2C%20who%20overpromised%20in%20the%20company's%20early%20days%2C%20Wadhwa%20is%20starting%20small.%20He's%20brought%20on%20advisers%20from%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%2C%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%20and%20Massachusetts%20General%20Hospital%20to%20try%20to%20prove%20out%20the%20concept.%20So%20far%2C%20he's%20spent%20about%20%24500%2C000%20of%20his%20own%20cash%20on%20the%20initiative%20and%20plans%20to%20spend%20%24500%2C000%20more%2C%20dipping%20into%20his%20retirement%20savings%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20having%20a%20working%20prototype%20later%20this%20year%20or%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20device%20works%2C%20such%20a%20tool%20could%20substantially%20improve%20certain%20types%20of%20cancer%20screening%20and%20allow%20for%20earlier%20detection%20in%20underserved%20communities%2C%20though%20plenty%20of%20obstacles%20remain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wadhwa%2C%2066%2C%20was%20born%20in%20India%20and%20immigrated%20to%20the%20US%20where%20he%20joined%20the%20technology%20industry.%20He%20founded%20two%20companies%20and%20wrote%20five%20books%2C%20along%20with%20a%20spate%20of%20prestigious%20teaching%20jobs%20including%20a%20stint%20as%20head%20of%20faculty%20at%20the%20now-embattled%20Singularity%20University%2C%20dedicated%20to%20solving%20the%20world's%20problems%20through%20entrepreneurship.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wadhwa's%20career%20as%20a%20public%20commentator%20won%20both%20him%20fame%20and%20notoriety.%20In%20a%20series%20of%20opinion%20columns%20in%20the%20Washington%20Post%20in%20the%202010s%20he%20had%20a%20habit%20of%20taking%20positions%20that%20rankled%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%20establishment.%20Among%20them%3A%20drawing%20attention%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20meritocracy%20in%20tech%2C%20long%20before%20racial%20and%20gender%20disparities%20became%20accepted%20fact.%20He%20also%20launched%20efforts%20to%20promote%20women%20in%20the%20industry%20-%20though%20critics%20said%20his%20advocacy%20could%20be%20condescending%2C%20and%20he%20eventually%20said%20he'd%20let%20women%20lead%20the%20charge%20on%20the%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wadhwa's%20life%20as%20a%20Silicon%20Valley%20chronicler%20changed%20when%20his%20wife%2C%20Tavinder%2C%20started%20feeling%20unwell%20during%20a%20family%20holiday%20in%20Mexico%20in%202018%2C%20and%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20a%20rare%20form%20of%20cancer.%20She%20soon%20entered%20chemotherapy%2C%20underwent%20genomic%20sequencing%20and%20tried%20various%20drugs%2C%20both%20established%20and%20experimental.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20diagnosis%2C%20Mr%20Wadhwa%20started%20dedicating%20much%20of%20his%20time%20to%20learning%20about%20the%20disease.%20He%20called%20on%20friends%20and%20professional%20acquaintances%2C%20talking%20with%20Siddhartha%20Mukherjee%2C%20author%20of%20The%20Emperor%20of%20All%20Maladies%2C%20who%20educated%20him%20on%20the%20limits%20of%20genomic%20sequencing.%20He%20also%20had%20conversations%20with%20tech%20titans%20who%20have%20taken%20a%20personal%20interest%20in%20health.%20These%20people%20include%20Sean%20Parker%2C%20the%20Napster%20co-founder%20who's%20now%20an%20active%20donor%20to%20cancer%20research%20with%20a%20particular%20focus%20on%20immunotherapy.%20Mr%20Parker%20%26quot%3Bspent%20many%20hours%20teaching%20me%20the%20basics%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20friends%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wadhwa's%20eventual%20conclusion%3A%20Doctors%20need%20a%20tool%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20conduct%20on-site%20tests%20that%20provide%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20detail%20compared%20with%20current%20tests.%20He%20wanted%20a%20device%20that%20is%20portable%2C%20costs%20%245%2C000%20or%20less%2C%20consumes%20no%20more%20than%20100%20watts%20and%20can%20produce%20results%20in%20under%20five%20minutes%20-%20all%20in%20a%20box%20that%20is%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20a%20desktop%20printer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20reasons%20that%20vision%20will%20be%20difficult%20to%20realize.%20%26quot%3BBreath%20measurement%20is%20tricky%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alex%20Morgan%2C%20a%20venture%20capitalist%20at%20Khosla%20Ventures%2C%20who%20has%20not%20reviewed%20Wadhwa's%20company.%20Morgan%20has%20invested%20in%20Invoy%20LLC%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20uses%20breath%20to%20measure%20ketones%2C%20chemicals%20emitted%20when%20the%20body%20is%20burning%20fat.%20Other%20companies%20working%20on%20breath%20diagnostics%20include%20the%20UK's%20Owlstone%20Medical.%20And%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%20at%20Boulder%2C%20researchers%20recently%20published%20their%20results%20on%20a%20laser-based%20breathalyzer%20that%20detects%20Covid-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20this%20July%2C%20Mr%20Wadhwa%20was%20ready%20to%20start%20a%20company%20dedicated%20to%20cancer%20detection%2C%20and%20incorporated%20Vionix.%20He%20initially%20thought%20he%20would%20start%20with%20blood%20tests%2C%20but%20he%20changed%20his%20mind%20after%20consulting%20with%20diagnostics%20specialists%20including%20Vionix's%20chief%20scientific%20officer%2C%20genome%20scientist%20Binay%20Panda.%20He%20learned%20that%20breath%20may%20include%20compounds%20related%20to%20lung%20cancer%2C%20breast%20cancer%20and%20others.%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20thought%20that%20there%20was%20so%20much%20information%20in%20breath%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20update%20to%20a%20handful%20of%20supporters%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20Vionix%20can%20handle%20breath%20tests%20-%20itself%20a%20large%20and%20unproven%20undertaking%20-%20it%20plans%20to%20move%20on%20to%20blood%20tests%2C%20urine%20tests%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20saliva%20tests%2C%20all%20done%20on%20the%20same%20device%20and%20using%20a%20cold%20plasma-based%20process%20Wadhwa%20has%20licensed%20from%20a%20group%20in%20Chile.%20The%20process%2C%20which%20will%20use%20artificial%20intelligence%20to%20recognize%20key%20characteristics%20of%20disease%2C%20in%20theory%20will%20make%20it%20possible%20to%20detect%20more%20biomarkers%20than%20existing%20tools%2C%20more%20accurately.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20Vionix%20device%20would%20be%20portable%2C%20Mr%20Wadhwa%20aims%20to%20operate%20both%20inside%20and%20outside%20of%20clinics.%20A%20portable%20tool%20would%20be%20particularly%20useful%20in%20poor%20or%20rural%20populations%20said%20Keith%20Flaherty%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%20and%20the%20director%20of%20clinical%20research%20at%20Massachusetts%20General%20Hospital's%20cancer%20center.%20Flaherty%2C%20a%20Vionix%20advisor%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20approach%20feels%20like%20stepping%20into%20a%20time%20machine%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20cautioned%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20way%20too%20soon%20to%20tell%26quot%3B%20if%20the%20technology%20will%20work%20as%20hoped.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELongtime%20Silicon%20Valley%20watchers%20will%20remember%20that%20Elizabeth%20Holmes%20made%20bold%20statements%20about%20her%20blood-testing%20company%2C%20Theranos%2C%20which%20ended%20with%20charges%20of%20fraud%20and%20the%20company's%20collapse%20after%20investors%20had%20poured%20in%20%249%20billion.%20Wadhwa%20says%20that%20in%20part%20because%20of%20Theranos'%20legacy%2C%20his%20policy%20will%20be%20to%20get%20outside%20researchers%20to%20use%20Vionix%20and%20document%20their%20results%2C%20rather%20than%20validating%20the%20machine%20in-house.%20%26quot%3BNo%20secrecy%2C%20no%20ethical%20lapses%2C%20no%20obsessions%20with%20making%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20said%20that%2C%20if%20I%20raise%20money%2C%20I%20am%20going%20to%20build%20a%20profitable%20company%20which%20could%20be%20worth%20billions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToward%20the%20end%20of%20his%20wife's%20illness%2C%20Mr%20Wadhwa%20said%20she%20asked%20him%20to%20prevent%20other%20people%20from%20suffering%20the%20same%20way.%20Despite%20an%20aggressive%20course%20of%20treatment%2C%20she%20died%20the%20summer%20after%20her%20diagnosis.%20She%20was%2057.%20Earlier%20detection%20could%20have%20led%20to%20a%20different%20outcome%2C%20Mr%20Wadhwa%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHer%20words%20and%20thoughts%20gave%20me%20the%20motivation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.