s%20by%20falsely%20inflating%20his%20property%20values%2C%20committing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-new-york-judge-finds-business-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyears%20of%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Engoron%20has%20already%20handed%20down%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-fraud-ruling-corporate-death-penalty-for-his-empire-experts-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecorporate%20death%20penalty%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20but%20the%20bench%20trial%20continues%20to%20decide%20the%20still%20outstanding%20parts%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-ny-fraud-trial-opens-today-heres-why-still-matters-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENew%20York%20attorney%20general's%20lawsuit%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20repeatedly%20denied%20wrongdoing%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20penalties%20for%20violating%20the%20gag%20order%20include%20fines%20and%20even%20prison%20time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20a%20legal%20expert%20told%20Insider%20that%20Trump%20is%20unlikely%20to%20face%20those%20types%20of%20consequences%2C%20even%20if%20the%20judge%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-understandably-looks-bored-at-his-250-million-fraud-trial-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efraud%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20finds%20he%20has%20broken%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrial%20attorney%20Bernard%20Alexander%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20Los%20Angeles-based%20firm%20of%20Alexander%20Morrison%20%2B%20Fehr%20LLP%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20gag%20orders%20are%20very%20uncommon%2C%20often%20reserved%20for%20high-profile%20cases%20where%20the%20Court%20is%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20protect%20the%20right%20to%20a%20fair%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%2C%20who%20has%20been%20an%20attorney%20for%20more%20than%2030%20years%20and%20specializes%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ordered-to-pay-32m-former-employee-race-discrimination-case-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20law%20and%20civil%20rights%20cases%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20court%20has%20several%20different%20options%20for%20how%20it%20can%20sanction%20Trump%20if%20he%20violates%20the%20gag%20order.%20Any%20decision%20the%20court%20makes%2C%20he%20said%2C%20will%20have%20to%20balance%20his%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20against%20the%20legal%20objective%20of%20achieving%20a%20fair%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20one%20thing%2C%20the%20judge%20can%20prevent%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20from%20presenting%20certain%20evidence.%20But%20judges%20prefer%20not%20to%20put%20their%20thumb%20on%20the%20scales%20of%20justice%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnother%20option%20is%20for%20the%20judge%20to%20inform%20the%20jury%20that%20Trump%20has%20violated%20his%20order.%20The%20judge%20could%20instruct%20the%20jury%20to%20consider%20that%20conduct%20and%20give%20it%20the%20weight%20that%20the%20jury%20thinks%20it%20deserves%20in%20considering%20Trump's%20evidence%20and%20credibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20added%20that%20the%20court%20could%20impose%20a%20fine%20%26quot%3Bbut%20that%20would%20be%20meaningless%26quot%3B%20given%20Trump's%20wealth%2C%20and%20said%20that%20judges%20in%20civil%20matters%20generally%20don't%20order%20people%20to%20go%20to%20jail%2C%20so%20the%20judge%20will%20have%20to%20be%20creative%20in%20implementing%20a%20sanction%20that%20would%20work%20to%20dissuade%20Trump%20from%20continuing%20to%20violate%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20has%20money%20and%20he%20uses%20it%20to%20bully%20people.%20He%20can%20keep%20paying%20fines%20amounting%20to%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20would%20have%20to%20be%20imposed%20in%20a%20case%20like%20this%20%E2%80%93%20without%20giving%20it%20a%20second%20thought%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20sanction%20must%20be%20something%20effective%20to%20reign%20Trump%20in%2C%20in%20order%20for%20him%20to%20take%20it%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20remains%20unclear%20exactly%20what%20the%20consequences%20may%20be%20if%20Trump%20violates%20the%20gag%20order%20against%20him%2C%20Alexander%20said%20he%20was%20not%20surprised%20by%20the%20order%20being%20issued%20and%20said%20that%20it%20was%20the%20right%20move%20by%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20judge%20is%20trying%20to%20maintain%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20court%20and%20proceed%20with%20as%20light%20a%20touch%20as%20possible%20to%20allow%20the%20case%20to%20progress%20without%20any%20hint%20that%20the%20court%20is%20being%20impartial.%20The%20more%20Trump%20violates%20the%20rules%2C%20the%20more%20the%20judge%20has%20to%20act%20to%20maintain%20integrity%20and%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20parties%20have%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20latitude%20in%20being%20able%20to%20criticize%20the%20court%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20judge.%20But%20singling%20out%20a%20court%20employee%20in%20a%20way%20that%20might%20encourage%20Trump's%20supporters%20to%20individually%20attack%20or%20intimidate%20the%20employee%20is%20unacceptable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgag-order-trump-fraud-case-consequences-unlikely-violation-legal-analysis-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696392951000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651cb833617692f0d03e7aea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgag-order-trump-fraud-case-consequences-unlikely-violation-legal-analysis-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Th