20speaker%20pro%20tem%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20Kalt%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%20told%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20having%20a%20speaker%20in%20line%20is%20that%20they%20were%20elected%20as%20speaker%2C%20not%20just%20appointed%20by%20someone%20to%20preside%20temporarily.%20So%2C%20as%20I%20read%20the%20statute%2C%20section%2019%20of%20title%203%2C%20Patty%20Murray%20is%20next%20in%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20House%20Republicans%20for%20the%20time%20being%20would%20be%20skipped%20over%20entirely.%20If%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20were%20unable%20to%20serve%20as%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20power%20would%20then%20fall%20to%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Patty%20Murray%2C%20Speaker%20Pro%20Tempore%20(not%20to%20be%20confused%20with%20McHenry's%20temporary%20title)%20and%20then%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20following%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurray's%20status%20was%20also%20the%20result%20of%20some%20drama%20as%20before%20her%20death%20Sen.%20Dianne%20Feinstein%20would%20have%20been%20the%20likely%20senator%20to%20claim%20it.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-democrats-dianne-feinstein-patty-murray-president-pro-tempore-2022-12%5C%22%3EFeinstein%20ultimately%20passed%20on%20the%20opportunity.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20any%20disputes%20would%20likely%20be%20settled%20in%20the%20courts%2C%20though%20Kalt%20stressed%20that%20it%20is%20clear%20McHenry%20does%20not%20have%20a%20claim%20to%20the%20presidency%20should%20it%20arise.%20McHenry's%20office%2C%20which%20is%20understandably%20busy%20right%20now%2C%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20McCarthy%20is%20the%20first%20speaker%20to%20be%20removed%20from%20power%20in%20this%20fashion%2C%20the%20concept%20of%20skipping%20over%20an%20official%20in%20the%20line%20of%20succession%20is%20nothing%20new.%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Madeline%20Albright%20would%20have%20been%20skipped%20over%20if%20she%20had%20the%20line%20of%20succession%20reached%20her%20during%20the%20Clinton%20administration%20since%20she%20did%20not%20meet%20the%20%26quot%3Bnatural%20born%20citizen%26quot%3B%20requirement%20to%20be%20president.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENever%20before%20in%20history%20has%20the%20line%20of%20succession%20gone%20past%20the%20vice%20president%2C%20meaning%20most%20of%20this%20discussion%20is%20purely%20academic.%C2%A0Still%2C%20House%20Republicans%20are%20currently%20risking%20what%20they%20would%20be%20rightfully%20entitled%20to%20thanks%20to%20their%20slim%20majority%20following%20the%202022%20midterm%20elections.%20If%20Biden%20and%20Harris%20were%20permanently%20unable%20to%20serve%2C%20Murray%20would%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20remain%20as%20acting%20president%20through%20January%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20where%20the%20current%20situation%20makes%20things%20really%20dicey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Presidential%20Succession%20Act%20allows%20for%20officials%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bbumped%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20that%20Murray%20or%20another%20lower-ranking%20official%20would%20be%20booted%20from%20office%20as%20soon%20as%20a%20new%20House%20speaker%20is%20elected.%20Many%20legal%20scholars%20have%20long%20had%20issues%20with%20the%20Truman-era%20law%20governing%20presidential%20succession.%20Some%20have%20questioned%20whether%20bumping%20someone%20from%20the%20presidency%20is%20even%20constitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20very%20least%2C%20the%20nation%20could%20be%20faced%20with%20a%20defining%20court%20battle%20as%20it%20copes%20with%20whatever%20chaos%20led%20to%20the%20president%20and%20vice%20president%20being%20unable%20to%20serve.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkevin-mccarthy-ouster-line-of-succession-h