e-for-first-time-in-history-12976003%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Should%20Be%20Transparent'%3A%20SC%20Says%20ED%20Must%20Provide%20Grounds%20for%20Arrest%20in%20Writing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29180215%2FThe-Wire-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Saying%20that%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20should%20transparent%20and%20above%20board%20in%20functioning%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20October%203%2C%20held%20that%20the%20agency%20should%20furnish%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20to%20the%20accused%20in%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20hold%20that%20it%20would%20be%20necessary%2C%20henceforth%2C%20that%20a%20copy%20of%20written%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20is%20furnished%20to%20the%20arrested%20person%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20course%20and%20without%20exception%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20A.S.%20Bopanna%20and%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fed-cant-be-vindictive-grounds-of-arrest-must-be-furnished-in-writing-to-accused-at-the-time-of-arrest-supreme-court-239238%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20top%20court%20also%20set%20aside%20the%20arrest%20of%20real%20estate%20group%20M3M%E2%80%99s%20directors%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20and%20Basant%20Bansal%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20said%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20%E2%80%9Creeks%20of%20arbitrariness%E2%80%9D%20and%20directed%20the%20immediate%20release%20of%20both%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20slammed%20the%20agency%20for%20its%20approach%20in%20the%20instant%20case%20to%20not%20furnish%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20to%20the%20accused%20in%20written%20form%20and%20instead%20reading%20them%20out.%20This%2C%20the%20court%20said%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20does%20not%20fulfil%20the%20mandate%20of%20Article%2022(1)%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20Section%2019(1)%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20observed%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20chronology%20of%20events%20speaks%20volumes%20and%20reflects%20rather%20poorly%2C%20if%20not%20negatively%2C%20on%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20functioning.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftracking-the-ed-case-by-case-puzzling-questions-emerge-in-its-handling-of-opposition-leaders%5C%22%3ETracking%20the%20ED%20Case%20by%20Case%2C%20Puzzling%20Questions%20Emerge%20in%20Its%20Handling%20of%20Opposition%20Leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20the%20ED%20%E2%80%9Chas%20to%20be%20transparent%2C%20above%20board%20and%20conform%20to%20pristine%20standards%20of%20fair%20play%20in%20action%E2%80%A6%20and%20must%20be%20seen%20to%20be%20acting%20with%20utmost%20probity%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20be%20expected%20to%20be%20vindictive.%20The%20judges%20said%20that%20the%20mere%20passing%20of%20an%20order%20of%20remand%20is%20not%20sufficient%20grounds%20to%20valide%20an%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20says%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CBeing%20a%20premier%20investigating%20agency%20charged%20with%20the%20onerous%20responsibility%20of%20curbing%20debilitating%20economic%20offence%20of%20money%20laundering%20in%20our%20country%2C%20every%20action%20of%20the%20ED%20in%20the%20course%20of%20such%20exercise%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20transparent%2C%20above%20board%20and%20conforming%20to%20the%20pristine%20standards%20of%20fair%20play%20in%20action.%20The%20ED%20mantled%20with%20far-reaching%20powers%20under%20the%20stringent%20Act%20of%202002%2C%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20be%20vindictive%20in%20its%20conduct%20and%20must%20be%20seen%20to%20be%20acting%20with%20utmost%20probity%20and%20with%20the%20highest%20degree%20of%20dispassion%20and%20fairness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20the%20ED%20has%20been%20granted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftracking-the-ed-case-by-case-puzzling-questions-emerge-in-its-handling-of-opposition-leaders%5C%22%3Eextraordinary%20powers%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20amendments%20to%20the%20PMLA%2C%20which%20crticis%20say%20allows%20the%20agency%20to%20be%20misused%20to%20target%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20opponents.%20Unlike%20any%20other%20investigative%20agency%2C%20the%20ED%20does%20not%20need%20to%20make%20a%20disclosure%20to%20a%20person%20to%20inform%20them%20whether%20they%20consider%20them%20a%20suspect%20or%20a%20witness.%20There%20is%20also%20no%20protection%20against%20a%20self-incriminating%20confession.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20ED%20also%20does%20not%20have%20magisterial%20oversight%20and%20the%20agency%20does%20not%20have%20to%20provide%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Case%20Information%20Report%20(ECIR)%2C%20the%20equivalent%20of%20an%20FIR%2C%20to%20the%20accused%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%2014%20opposition%20parties%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fopposition-petition-supreme-court-cbi-ed%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20petition%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20alleged%20misues%20of%20central%20agencies%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20They%20said%20since%202014%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20exponential%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20registered%20by%20the%20ED%20%E2%80%93%20and%20most%20of%20them%20against%20critics%20and%20opponents%20of%20the%20Modi%20regime.%20But%20the%20conviction%20rate%20under%20the%20PMLA%20is%20abysmally%20low%2C%20the%20petition%20argued%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Conly%2023%20convictions%20under%20the%20PMLA%20have%20been%20secured%E2%80%9D.%20The%20top%20court%20turned%20the%20petition%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696351716000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29180215%2FThe-Wire-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-ed-transparency-vindictive%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20said%20that%20the%20chronology%20of%20events%20in%20the%20arrest%20of%20real%20estate%20barons%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20and%20Basant%20Bansal%20%26quot%3Bspeaks%20volumes%20and%20reflects%20rather%20poorly%2C%20if%20not%20negatively%2C%20on%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20functioning.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-ed-transparency-vindictive%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UAPA%20case%3A%20NewsClick%20chief%20arrested%20and%2046%20quizzed%3B%20office%20sealed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696350617000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F09%2Ffull%2F1691587876-9509.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fuapa-case-newsclick-chief-arrested-and-46-quizzed-office-sealed-123100301374_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Oppn%2C%20media%20bodies%20term%20it%20assault%20on%20press%3B%20action%20on%20basis%20of%20evidence%3A%20BJP%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fuapa-case-newsclick-chief-arrested-and-46-quizzed-office-sealed-123100301374_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fuapa-case-newsclick-chief-arrested-and-46-quizzed-office-sealed-123100301374_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fuapa-case-newsclick-chief-